This describes me mostly. I am up for communicating, talking about anything, but not interested in having my time wasted with dickery and likely to come off as stuck up unless I am making an effort to mingle; that's not a diss to you I am just likely spaced out thinking about problems and/or off my face and the walls are melting. The only other thing I would like is if it had banned topic and a level of intimacy with strangers I am okay with: mensa meetings have something similar to this.<br />
<br />
Ideally something like what it already is then:<br />
<br />
- Not interested in banal small talk (such as the weather which I can look up in &lt; .1 seconds with more authoritative information)<br />
- Politics, ever<br />
- Qualitative circle jerks outside of philosophy<br />
<br />
- Most interested in talking about<b></b>:<br />
Math, Philosophy, Mythology, Literature, System Design, Coffee, Nootropics, Security, Program Analysis, Farming, Control Systems, Cults, and why Gwern.net rocks the casbah<br />
<br />
- Lets keep it to hand shakes maximum, no exceptions*; bubble decreases the more we know one another, don't cough or sneeze on me and wash your hands cause Jesus and germs are everywhere. <br />
- I am not interested in a romantic relationship with you, no exceptions. <br />
<br />
* Unless we are fucking, don't touch me past the palm and your palm or chest bumps if we are bros/sisters!</div>

